<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Shrubs often sprout following fire from lignotubers, but fire kills year-old seedlings. Seedlings emerge from the seed bank in the first season after fire, but reported densities are low. However, high-intensity fires kill seeds, and repeated burning kills mature plants (Montalvo 2002c).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Medium (15-70+ years)
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Seasonality</td>
			<td>Late summer-fall
				
			</td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Size/extent</td>
			<td>Medium to large; up to or beyond stand size
				
